S ix teenage girls were confirmed dead yesterday in Kebbi State as a result of canoe mishap.  Confirming the incident to newsmen in Birnin Kebbi, the local government Chairman of Suru, Alhaji Umaru Maigandi, said that the incident occurred when the canoe capsized while ferrying the victims across Tindifai River on Monday. According to him, the canoe left Tindifai village conveying nine girls to a Fadama area where they were going to harvest rice but it capsized along the way.  “The village is close to Bendu in Tundifai; they were going to harvest rice in the Fadama area when the incident occurred and resulted to the death of the six females.The deceased were between the ages of 12 years and 15 years. The three other victims were rescued alive by the driver of the canoe, Umar Faruk, a 13-year-old.  “The deceased had been buried according to Islamic rites, and we have condoled the families as well as sympathised with those that survived the mishap,” he said. Maigari, who attributed the incident to overloading, added that the canoe was overloaded as it had five-passenger capacity. The chairman said the council would sensitize the communities to the dangers of overloading canoes, particularly those in the riverine communities of the state.